      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BELTONE BOY (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at this track behind Speed Dial (23.10) in a Grade 4/5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Key chance in this line up. LATE IN ARRIVAL (6) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in three starts, including two wins. Placed last time (22.81) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 5.5 lengths. Looks one of the chances. HOMER MULWEE (2) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 6 lengths away in third (22.88) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Hard to beat again. MINTER MULWEE (7) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
